# Dependencies & Tooling Currency

- Canonical note: `docs/90-Meta/collaboration-and-decision-protocol.md`
  (§ Dependencies & tooling currency). This rule is an orchestrator; the vault wins.
- **Binding, never optional.** Use the **latest stable** version of every library,
  framework and tool, and stay current — for features, future-proofing and security.
- **Docs-first:** before adding *or upgrading* anything, read current docs + best
  practices via **context7** and **Ref (ref.tools)** (plus Perplexity/Web). Verify
  the real latest version (release notes / `git ls-remote --tags` / default branch);
  never assume an API, default, or which version is "latest".
- **Pin exact, update regularly:** exact pins, no floating `latest`/ranges (ADR-0021);
  currency via regular reviewed bumps (Renovate).
- **HITL:** staying on an outdated version, or any upgrade/migration that cannot be
  done without major complications, is escalated to Nico — an agent never decides it
  alone; record the outcome (ADR / Decision-Log).
